        authenticityMarker: "The Basque boarding house tradition of the Mother Lode — operating at establishments like the National Hotel in Jackson and various remaining Basque establishments — serves communal meals to any paying guest at long tables, a direct transplant of the Pyrenean shepherd communal eating tradition; the lamb is sourced from flocks that still graze the Sierra foothill rangeland under Basque family management."
