        authenticityMarker: "Sacramento River white sturgeon — Acipenser transmontanus — is native to the Pacific drainages and was historically so abundant in the Sacramento and San Joaquin rivers that it constituted a major food source for Valley Miwok and Maidu peoples; commercial wild harvest has been restricted since the 1990s, but Delta aquaculture operations now produce both the smoked fish and the caviar in a single facility that is unique in American inland aquaculture."
